-1 PAINTBALL PBWARSTAT WAR JOINPBWAR SHOOT RELOAD EXITPBWAR~
Paintball has come to Ghost Dancer! Paintball was the brain child of our
very own Lessy who flushed out the details of the game and its rules. It
has been coded by Taka.

PBWARSTAT
This command shows the status of all combatants in the paintball war and it
lists the kills they have made and the deaths they have suffered.

WAR
This is the war channel used by combatants and non-combatants alike to request
a war or better yet roleplay leading to a war.
Use this exactliy like you would gossip: WAR <message>

JOINPBWAR
This command allows you to join an existing paintball war while it is in the
join phase. This is a 3 tick period just before the war begins. After these
3 ticks are over noone may join a paintball game.

SHOOT 
Shoot is used to shoot at a victim. You have a chance at hitting them with
your paintball. 
use it like kill: SHOOT <victim>

RELOAD
You only get so many shoots before you are out of ammo. When this happens use
reload to "reload" your ammo.

EXITPBWAR
Allows the character to exit a paintball war already in progress.

In the game of paintball you will be the hunted and the hunter. If you shoot
someone they cannot shoot you nor can you shoot them again. You can kill as
many people playing as there are, but you can only kill each person once.
But beware they could kill you first!
~

102 STRPBWAR ENDPBWAR~
STRPBWAR
Use this to start a paintball war. You can name the number of ticks or let it
default to the preset number for the mud. So to start a paintball war that
will last 10 ticks you would type this: STRPBWAR 10

ENDPBWAR
This command ends immediately the paintball war inprogress.
~

